pressure determines molecular gas properties. Third, the turbulence
driven by feedback processes in {GMCs} makes star formation slow, allowing
a small fraction of the gas to be converted to stars per free-fall time
within the molecular clouds. We combine analytic estimates for each of
these steps to formulate a single star formation law, and show that the
predicted correlation between {SFR,} metallicity, and surface densities of
atomic, molecular, and total gas agree well with observations.},
