spectral energy distributions of some of the high-z galaxies (2.4
{\textless}{\textasciitilde}z{\textless}{\textasciitilde} 2.9) observed with the Spitzer Space Telescope by Yan et al.
Their high rest-frame {near-IR} fluxes is reproduced very well with the
models including {TP-AGB} stars for ages in the range {{\textasciitilde}0.6-1.5Gyr,}
suggesting formation redshifts for these objects around z{\textasciitilde} 3-6.},
