haloes are identified in the simulations. This bias function is
sufficient to calculate the cross-correlation between dark haloes and
mass, and again we find excellent agreement between simulation results
and analytic predictions. Because haloes are spatially exclusive, the
variance in the count of objects within spheres of fixed radius and
overdensity is significantly smaller than the Poisson value. This
seriously complicates any analytic calculation of the autocorrelation
