masses of discs are a few per cent of those of their haloes; (ii) the 
specific angular momenta of discs are similar to those of their haloes; 
(iii) present-day discs were assembled recently (at z{\textless}=1). In 
particular, the observed scatter in the size-rotation velocity plane is 
